<paragraph id="1E1236950E88FF2DFCBDAEBDFD9EFEF8" blockId="179.[820,1436,1453,1904]" lastBlockId="180.[143,759,195,278]" lastPageId="180" lastPageNumber="321" pageId="179" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis id="2CD9EA870E88FF2AFCBDAEBDFC49FA2F" box="[820,948,1453,1474]" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="320">Discussion:</emphasis>
Bader overlooked the presence of dorsal plates in a slide preparation of 
<taxonomicName id="D9AD4D160E88FF2AFB11AEDCFAE4FA0D" authorityName="Piersig" authorityYear="1898" box="[1176,1305,1483,1505]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Megapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="179" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricatus">
<emphasis id="2CD9EA870E88FF2AFB11AEDCFAE4FA0D" box="[1176,1305,1483,1505]" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="320">A. loricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
authorized by Piersig (here designated as 
<typeStatus id="C11688370E88FF2AFB2BAEFAFAF5F9ED" box="[1186,1288,1514,1536]" pageId="179" pageNumber="320">lectotype</typeStatus>
of that species), convincing himself in the process that 
<bibRefCitation id="7A3C4B640E88FF2AFAB0AD19FC18F9D0" author="Motas C &amp; Angelier C" pageId="179" pageNumber="320" pagination="121 - 137" refId="ref179134" refString="Motas C, Angelier C. 1927. Hydracariens recueillis dans le Massif Central. Travaux du Laboratoire d'Hydrobiologie et de Pisciculture d l'Universite de Grenoble 19: 121 - 137." type="journal article" year="1927">Motaş &amp; Angelier (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, together with all subsequent authors, had a mistaken concept of the species. He introduced a new name for all the material published under that name since then. His idea was that 
<taxonomicName id="D9AD4D160E88FF2AFB6AAD94FA66F975" box="[1251,1435,1667,1689]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="179" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="placocallosus">
<emphasis id="2CD9EA870E88FF2AFB6AAD94FA66F975" box="[1251,1435,1667,1689]" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="320">A. placocallosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be a species with typical dorsal muscle attachment sclerites (as described many times for 
<taxonomicName id="D9AD4D160E88FF2AFABAADD1FCAAF918" authorityName="Piersig" authorityYear="1898" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Megapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="179" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricatus">
<emphasis id="2CD9EA870E88FF2AFABAADD1FCAAF918" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="320">A. loricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and a sclerotized excretory pore. He came close to actually introducing a valid new species because, in contrast to the established opinion about the morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="D9AD4D160E88FF2AFC19AC2CFBE6F8BD" authorityName="Piersig" authorityYear="1898" box="[912,1051,1851,1873]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Megapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="179" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricatus">
<emphasis id="2CD9EA870E88FF2AFC19AC2CFBE6F8BD" box="[912,1051,1851,1873]" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="320">A. loricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the type revision reveals the absence of an anal sclerite. However, a further error clearly occurred when he selected the 
<typeStatus id="C11688370E8FFF2DFDD7ABD3FD3EFF34" box="[606,707,195,217]" pageId="180" pageNumber="321">holotype</typeStatus>
: the slide-mounted specimen represents 
<taxonomicName id="D9AD4D160E8FFF2DFDAEABF2FD69FF1B" baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[551,660,225,247]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="180" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="walteri">
<emphasis id="2CD9EA870E8FFF2DFDAEABF2FD69FF1B" box="[551,660,225,247]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="321">A. walteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and not a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="D9AD4D160E8FFF2DFEDCAA10FE44FEF8" authorityName="Piersig" authorityYear="1898" box="[341,441,256,277]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Megapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="180" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricatus">
<emphasis id="2CD9EA870E8FFF2DFEDCAA10FE44FEF8" box="[341,441,256,277]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="321">loricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
